This show was performed as part of a community radio promotion for the Willoughby’s Beach EP and featured the earliest confirmed performances of Danger $$$, Black Tooth, Let It Bleed, Dead-Beat, Dustbin Fletcher, and Willoughby’s Beach. Crookedile was dedicated to The Vasco Era vocalist Sid O’Neil (and Cook Craig). Let It Bleed was introduced as “not a Rolling Stones cover or anything”. Dustbin Fletcher was introduced as being “named after our favorite Essendon veteran”, a reference to Essendon Football Club defender Dustin Fletcher. Stoned Mullet was introduced as being named after a band Stu thought was “really cool” when he was in high school. KGLW.net Staff Notes: We note these as "first confirmed performances" of most of these songs due in part to so few King Gizzard recordings from this time period. Public recordings of King Gizz from this time period are so rare that these distinctions should in no way be confused with debuts, which may have actually been much earlier. KGLW.net staff is 100% confident in "debuts" as the first time played live...unless its Satan Speeds Up, then we just have to trust what Stu says.

King Gizzard appeared as part of the Meredith Music Festival, a “dream” for the band. Elbow was "pretty different" compared to the final album recording. After Talk Talk Talk, Stu mentioned his new 12-string Stratocaster that was also featured in the Muckraker music video saying "it's sick". He mentions it again after High Hopes Low saying it was "really hard to tune". I Wanna Be Your Dog was sung to the tune of Crookedile. KGLW.net Staff Notes: The setlist for this show may be incomplete and out of order. Elbow was confirmed by Stu in a track-by-track for 12 Bar Bruise here, Black Tooth and Lunch Meat were reported by the linked reviews and Talk Talk Talk through I Wanna Be Your Dog were confirmed by the audio recording. The beginning of Talk Talk Talk is missing, and it is unknown if additional songs were played prior. If anyone has any information on what else may have been played at this show or, ideally, a complete or conclusive recording please contact KGLW.net staff at setlists@kglw.net.

This show was a performance for the New Year's Eve Esplanade celebration/festival. Elbow contained different lyrics to the finished release. After Black Tooth, Joey asked if anyone from the crowd is from Deniliquin. After Talk Talk Talk, Stu mentioned his new 12-string Stratocaster that was also featured in the Muckraker music video, saying that he "loves it, but it's really hard to tune". Before Dead-Beat, Enter Sandman (Metallica) was teased.

Gamma Knife and People Vultures contained alternate lyrics. Stressin' was performed solo by Stu after a raucous and sustained "One more song!" chant.

This was the Garage Rock Night show of the Princess Theatre residency, the fourth of five planned shows, each featuring a different specific genre and preannounced songs. This ended up being the final night of the residency as Metal Night, scheduled for December 23, 2021, was cancelled. The Lord of Lightning contained Cellophane teases. I’m Not In Your Mind contained Alter Me teases & quotes. Dead-Beat was played for the first time since 2015-06-26. (311 show gap) Black Tooth was played for the first time since 2015-09-13. (358 show gap) Wah Wah contained The River teases. Danger $$$ was played for the first time since 2018-10-04. (91 show gap) Muckraker was played for the first time since 2018-11-24. (84 show gap) Robot Stop contained Hot Water teases. Cut Throat Boogie was introduced as a song Ambrose wrote about the time Cookie bottled him. KGLW.net Staff Notes: The setlist for this show is believed to be complete, but only partial recordings exist. Recordings of Digital Black are unavailable and most other songs are incomplete. The missing songs were confirmed based on the preannounced song lists for each of the 5 planned genre specific shows and contemporaneous discussions through various social media, but any additional setlist notations that require audio confirmation (segues, quotes or teases) may be incomplete. If anyone has any further information or, ideally, a complete or conclusive recording please contact KGLW.net staff at setlists@kglw.net. Poster By Jason Galea Edition of 200

The show began with a chant of “fuck shit up” by the crowd, which was repeated several times throughout the show. Self-Immolate was introduced as a song about setting yourself on fire. Before starting Magenta Mountain the crowd’s chant was changed to “ma-gen-ta.” Slow Jam 1 contained Iron Lung quotes. Supreme Ascendancy was introduced as a song about “how much Amby loves our lord and savior…Satan!” SPELLLING and The Chats were shouted out after Oddlife. Following Ontology Stu and the audience had a discussion of the apple that Stu was eating during the show. The Lord of Lightning contained a Cellophane tease. Before Dead-Beat, Stu announced that they would be playing an older song. This announcement prompted several requests from the audience, including God is in the Rhythm, “Taste of an Orange” (Almacknjack) and “Stairway to Heaven” (Led Zeppelin) which was then teased by Joey, who then claimed that he had no idea how to play that song and referred to it as Stairway to Kevin. Am I in Heaven? contained Her and I (Slow Jam 2) teases, God Is Calling Me Back Home teases, The Dripping Tap teases/quotes, Boogieman Sam teases/quotes, Rattlesnake teases, Hot Wax quotes and Head On/Pill teases/quotes. KGLW.net Staff Notes: Special shout out to our very own @spidzzle for the recording located on Archive.org!
data.venuename: Event Lawn at Virgin Hotels Las Vegas

data.shownotes: This show featured the debut of Ice V. Wah Wah began with the intro to The River, and subsequently contained Crumbling Castle and The River teases. Ambrose quoted It Ain't Me, Babe (Bob Dylan) before Doom City. O.N.E. began with the intro to Straws in the Wind instead of the customary intro. Pleura contained a quote of “Freedom” (Rage Against the Machine). Straws in the Wind was dedicated to Russell Brand. Smoke and Mirrors was played over the PA as the setbreak music. Gaia featured a Cavs drum solo. Ambergris contained an Ice V tease. Before The Reticent Raconteur, Leah Senior was introduced to the stage as “The Original Balrog” and Joey gave a shoutout to her live bass player Jack [Robbins], with the bonus trivia that he was also in Stu’s first band Almacknjack. The Reticent Raconteur was played for the first time since 2021-02-24 (61 show gap). The Reticent Raconteur and The Lord of Lightning featured narration by Leah Senior. The Fourth Colour was played for the first time since 2019-11-23 (70 show gap). Am I in Heaven? contained The Dripping Tap teases. Poster by Jason Galea 800 standard / 50 Foil Print

Evil Death Roll contained You Can Be Your Silhouette and Field of Vision teases. Field of Vision was dedicated to the city of Nashville. Raw Feel contained a Witchcraft tease. Black Tooth was played for the first time since 2022-10-02. (118 show gap) Le Risque was dedicated to Johnny Cash. I'm Not In Your Mind featured Ambrose on sax. Hot Wax contained a Am I In Heaven? tease. After I'm In Your Mind Fuzz, Stu thanked Trey [Anastasio] because a fan threw a shirt on stage of the Phish logo with the letters altered to say Gizz. Slow Jam 1 featured Ambrose on sax and Hypertension, You Can Be Your Sillouhette, and Witchcraft teases. Perihelion featured Jay Weinberg (formerly of Slipknot) on drums. Chang'e contained an intro jam with Extinction quotes and the song itself contained Witchcraft quotes. Extinction contained an Intergalactic (Beastie Boys) quote.

Poster by Jason Galea
Standard Edition - 650
Foil Edition - 200

Wah Wah contained a The River intro with a Cellophane tease and the song itself contained a The River quote as well as a jam and Am I In Heaven? teases. 
Before Antarctica, which was introduced as a song about Antarctica and "Cookie's biggest regret thinking polar bears live [there]", Ambrose quoted the outro of Daily Blues. Ambergris was dedicated to sperm whales. Trapdoor was introduced as a song about "the dungeon Stu keeps Ambrose trapped in to make music". Before Black Tooth, Stu asked the crowd if anyone had been to the nine Red Rocks shows the band had done, which led Ambrose to quote Nein and say they should play it. Before People-Vultures, Ambrose quoted Walk The Dinosaur (Was (Not Was)). People-Vultures itself contained Iron Lung quotes. Mr. Beat contained an Iron Lung jam with lyrics. Flight b741 was dedicated to Lucas. Theia contained The Silver Cord quotes. Gilgamesh contained Gila Monster quotes. Set contained Ice V teases. Float Along - Fill Your Lungs contained a Dragon jam. Garden Goblin was on the printed setlist after Set but was not played.

Poster by Jason Galea
Standard - 1200
Gold Foil - 300

Gaia featured a drum solo by Cavs. This Thing contained an Incredible (M Beat) quote. Crumbling Castle contained a Loyalty tease. The Fourth Colour contained teases of Whole Lotta Rosie (AC/DC) and Forty Six and 2 (Tool).  Nuclear Fusion's intro was sung by an audience member named Rob. Prior to Intrasport, Ambrose and Stu gave Lucas a shoutout for playing guitar on the track and Ambrose introduced a gong solo from Cavs. Set contained an Ice V tease. Ambrose introduced Antarctica as a song Cook wrote about his love of air conditioning. Joey tried to imitate Jacob Collier by instructing the audience to do throat singing before Black Tooth. Iron Lung contained People-Vultures teases.  Le Risque was introduced as a song about a little grey mouse and contained a Whole Lotta Rosie (AC/DC) tease. Boogieman Sam was preceded by teases of Riff Raff (AC/DC), Moby Dick (Led Zeppelin) and Whole Lotta Rosie (AC/DC), and contained a Whole Lotta Rosie (AC/DC) jam with Field of Vision quotes and Riff Raff (AC/DC) teases. This led to a People-Vultures jam with Muddy Water teases and Iron Lung and Phantom Island quotes.  Mirage City was on the written setlist after Antarctica but was not played.
